Class FeatureVectorObj

  • java.lang.Object
    • FeatureVectorObj
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class FeatureVectorObj
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    A FeatureVectorObj implements a mixed-type vector of integers, reals, and lists. Collectively, these vector elements define the high-level characteristics of a DomainTheory. This vector will be used to compare any two DomainTheories and compute their similarity. NOTE: All messages in this class are intended for the Developer or Administrator. They are not internationalized.

      • phiScore

        public double phiScore(double num,
              FeatureVectorObj.FloatDistributionObj distn)
        Implements a standard look-up table of values for the percent of the distribution area to the left of a value.
        Parameters:
        num - a real number drawn from the distribution.
        distn - the distribution of floats for this FeatureVector element, including num
        Returns:
        the statistical Phi-score. Taken from the table in a standard textbook (Jay L. Devore, Probability & Statistics 5, Pacific Grove CA, Duxbury)
